#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\starting_jaws_for_windows.htm+html.body.h1:17-1"
msgid "Starting JAWS for Windows"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:18-1
msgid ""
"After installing JAWS, you can configure it to start manually, or to launch "
"automatically when your computer starts. The latter is known as running JAWS "
"as a service. Starting automatically is useful for those who require speech "
"immediately."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:19-1
msgid "Manually Starting JAWS"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:20-1
msgid "To manually start JAWS, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:22-1
msgid "Press <strong>WINDOWS Key+R</strong> to open the Run dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:23-1
msgid ""
"Type \"JAWS<em>X</em>\" (where <em>X</em> is the version number) and press "
"<strong>ENTER</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:25-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Tip:</strong> To override your user settings and start JAWS with "
"only the default factory settings, type \"JAWS<em>X</em> /default\" (where "
"<em>X</em> is the version number). You can also assign a shortcut hot key to "
"the JAWS shortcut. For more information, please see <a href=\"tutorial.chm::/"
"windows_with_jfw_basics/desktop_orientation.htm#Define_a_Hotkey\">Define a "
"Hot Key</a>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:26-1
msgid "Automatically Starting JAWS"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:27-1
msgid ""
"When you first install JAWS, the JAWS Startup Wizard launches. The Run JAWS "
"Settings page in the wizard provides several options for starting JAWS. Use "
"the default settings on this page since these will ensure that JAWS always "
"loads, starts, and runs before and after Windows launches. If these settings "
"change and later you want to restore the default values, do the following so "
"that JAWS starts automatically:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:29-1
msgid ""
"Start JAWS manually as previously described, and press <strong>INSERT+J</"
"strong> to access the JAWS application window."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:30-1
msgid ""
"Press <strong>ALT+H</strong> to select the Help menu, and then <strong>Z</"
"strong> to launch the JAWS Startup Wizard."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:31-1
msgid ""
"Choose <strong>Next</strong> until the Run JAWS Settings page opens. If you "
"have an Administrator account, several options appear in the wizard. If you "
"have a Standard User account, only the <strong>Start JAWS after log on for "
"this user</strong> combo box appears."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:32-1
msgid "For an Administrator account, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:35-1
msgid "Select the Start JAWS at the Log On Screen check box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:36-1
msgid "Clear the Start JAWS after Log On for all Users check box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:37-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\starting_jaws_for_windows.htm+html.body.ul.li:37-1"
msgid "Select Always in the Start JAWS after Log On for this User combo box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:38-1
msgid "Clear the Run JAWS from System Tray check box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:40-1
msgid "For a Standard User account, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:42-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\starting_jaws_for_windows.htm+html.body.ul.li:42-1"
msgid "Select Always in the Start JAWS after Log On for this User combo box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:45-1
msgid ""
"Choose <strong>Next</strong> to continue through the remaining pages of the "
"wizard."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:46-1
msgid ""
"On the last page of the JAWS Startup Wizard, choose <strong>Finish</strong> "
"to accept the changes and close the wizard. The next time you start Windows, "
"JAWS starts automatically, and is one of the first programs available."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cstarting_jaws_for_windows.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:48-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Tip:</strong> If JAWS is configured to start automatically at the "
"logon screen or after you have logged into Windows, press and hold both the "
"<strong>LEFT SHIFT</strong> and <strong>RIGHT SHIFT</strong> keys as Windows "
"boots, or after you have logged in, to prevent JAWS from starting. This is "
"useful if you need to troubleshoot any startup related issues you may be "
"experiencing."
msgstr ""

